description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Occupational Therapist to join the St. Helier Occupational Therapy Rotation. Each rotation averages 6 months and currently includes General Medicine and Surgery, Orthopaedics, Care of the Elderly, and Acute Stroke, which is based at Epsom General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for candidates with the relevant knowledge and skills and an enthusiasm to deliver and develop the OT service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To deliver skilled occupational therapy services across acute care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will have clinical responsibility for assessment and treatment planning for people referred. They will be expected to participate in developing and monitoring the service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work closely with multidisciplinary teams and other professionals, particularly in relation to patient enablement, and to assist in the development of good working relationships with statutory, voluntary and independent organisations and agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To actively participate in audit, service progression and role development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To contribute to services provided during extended hours and weekends, on a rota basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Needs to be a Car Driver with Full Driving License.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLindsey HernandezJob titleAcute Therapy ManagersEmail addressLindsey.hernandez@nhs.netTelephone number020 8296 4387&lt;/p&gt;
